# RisingStack-bootcamp

**RisingStack-bootcamp** is a **REST API** which is using the 3rd version of GitHub API to get information of a repository by given ID or owner / name. You can also get the contributions to a certain repository by given ID or owner / name.

## How to use the endpoints of the API [/api/v1/]

### /api/v1/repository/:id [GET]

#### Gives back a repository by id

+ Parameteres
    + :id (integer) - ID of the selected repository in the form of an integer

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/repository/:id

    + Body

            {
                "id": 94214710,
                "owner": {
                    "id": 6916052,
                    "login": "RisingStack",
                    "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/6916052?v=4",
                    "html_url": "https://github.com/RisingStack",
                    "type": "Organization"
                },
                "full_name": "RisingStack/risingstack-bootcamp",
                "description": "This is the Node.js Bootcamp we ask new recruits at RisingStack to finish in their first weeks. It helps to get the basics right, and prepare you to work on enterprise projects.","html_url": "https://github.com/RisingStack/risingstack-bootcamp",
                "language": "JavaScript",
                "stargazers_count": 470
            }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

    + Headers

            Location: /api/v1/repository/:id

    + Body

            {
                "errors": {
                    "id": [ 
                        "\"id\" must be a number"
                    ]
                }
            }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

    + Headers
    
            Location: /api/v1/repository/:id
        
    + Body

            {
                body: "Not Found"
            }

